WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.860
Now, inside each of these pipeline stages,
there's a conversation

2
00:00:05.860 --> 00:00:12.320
happening. And every conversation you have
follows a five-step framework.

3
00:00:13.780 --> 00:00:17.100
Step one is the intro, where you set
expectations.

4
00:00:17.800 --> 00:00:21.740
You tell them who you are, why you're
calling, and what they'll get out of the

5
00:00:21.740 --> 00:00:22.540
conversation.

6
00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:29.160
Step two is the fact find, where you ask
questions, qualify, and listen.

7
00:00:29.780 --> 00:00:33.620
This is where you should be spending about
80% of your conversation time.

8
00:00:33.900 --> 00:00:37.540
And notice I said talking about the person,
not the house.

9
00:00:39.020 --> 00:00:43.860
Step three is the pitch, where you present
what BMH does.

10
00:00:44.360 --> 00:00:49.580
This is actually the only part of the
conversation that's really about the property and

11
00:00:49.580 --> 00:00:51.160
the transaction itself.

12
00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:56.800
Step four is the offer, where you transition
toward next steps.

13
00:00:57.060 --> 00:01:02.360
For you, that usually means teeing up the
handoff rather than throwing out a number.

14
00:01:03.660 --> 00:01:06.820
And step five is the close, where you get
commitment.

15
00:01:07.140 --> 00:01:11.480
That might be setting an appointment with
the acquisition team, getting agreement to

16
00:01:11.480 --> 00:01:14.940
receive an offer, or just locking in a firm
follow-up time.

17
00:01:15.860 --> 00:01:18.320
Here's the thing that ties all this
together.

18
00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:22.780
The pipeline stages are the organizational
structure.

19
00:01:22.980 --> 00:01:26.720
They tell you where a lead is in the overall
process.

20
00:01:27.180 --> 00:01:32.300
The five-step framework is how you actually
execute within each conversation.

21
00:01:33.180 --> 00:01:36.260
Pipeline stages move leads forward through
the system.

22
00:01:36.780 --> 00:01:40.400
Conversation steps move each individual call
forward.

23
00:01:41.300 --> 00:01:44.140
One more thing, and this is important.

24
00:01:44.660 --> 00:01:49.620
About 80% of your conversation should not
be about the property.

25
00:01:50.160 --> 00:01:54.640
Only about 20% should actually be about the
house itself.

26
00:01:55.100 --> 00:02:01.360
The rest is intro, rapport building, fact
finding, understanding the person.

27
00:02:01.580 --> 00:02:06.920
Because the house is not the problem, the
person's situation is the problem.

28
00:02:06.920 --> 00:02:12.700
Your job is to find the solution to their
problem, and the house just happens to be the

29
00:02:12.700 --> 00:02:14.600
vehicle for that solution.

30
00:02:15.980 --> 00:02:20.340
New people make the mistake of jumping straight
to, tell me about the house, and trying

31
00:02:20.340 --> 00:02:23.120
to race toward an offer as fast as possible.

32
00:02:23.620 --> 00:02:25.340
Don't do that. Slow down.

33
00:02:25.752 --> 00:02:26.848
Build the relationship.

34
00:02:27.220 --> 00:02:29.400
Actually care about what's going on.

35
00:02:29.900 --> 00:02:31.100
The deals will follow.

36
00:02:32.620 --> 00:02:34.780
Alright, let's keep going.

37
00:02:35.580 --> 00:02:40.200
Next up, we're going to break down exactly
how to open a call and run a fact find.
